(upcoming the duel video of this deck profile)

Konami seems to love Dinomorphia/Dinorphia, because they gave this deck a really weird tech option: The Supreme King's Soul. A Normal Trap that requires you to pay half your LP...in a control deck all about paying half your LP to activate Normal Traps.

&nbsp;

And if your opponent activates a Spell, you can banish Supreme King's Soul from your GY and ZAR-C from your field to summon Crystal Wing or Crystal Clear Wing from your Extra Deck! Crystal Wing and Crystal Clear Wing are both negates that can work during either player's turn, so they are by far the best targets for Supreme King's Soul that you can put in this Deck!

&nbsp;

And since Jurassic World: Dominion was trending on Twitter days ago...Well, you know why I named this deck "Dinomorphia Dominion."
